---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Uses — Christopher Rangel" description="The gear, software, and tools Christopher Rangel actually uses">
	<div class="container">
		<section class="hero">
			<h1>Uses</h1>
		</section>
		<div class="prose">
			<h3>Camera</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Sony A6000</li>
				<li>A variety of lenses, with a preference for lower apertures outside of portrait work</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Photo Editing</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Adobe Lightroom, primarily</li>
				<li>Photoshop, for occasional touch-ups</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Design</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Figma, plus the Figma MCP server for pulling designs straight into code</li>
				<li>Lucid, for flowcharts and diagramming</li>
				<li>Obsidian, for notes and knowledge management</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				My actual process leans on all three together: brainstorm with Claude, save the
				useful parts to Obsidian, then build with Claude Code in the terminal.
			</p>

			<h3>Development</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>VS Code</li>
				<li>Terminal, working with Claude Code and other agents</li>
				<li>Astro</li>
				<li>GitHub Pages</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>This Site</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Built with Astro v6</li>
				<li>Deployed on GitHub Pages</li>
				<li>No analytics, no trackers</li>
				<li>Set in Lora, with a system monospace stack for code and labels</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
</Base>
